  "text": "The DWG method is used as a primary example to the wave-based methods in this paper. Naturally, the KWconverter formulation is applicable to any W-method, such as the wave digital filters (WDFs) [CITATION_1] . In the future, we plan to extend our examples to include WDF excitation blocks. Other important future directions are the analysis of the dynamic behavior of parametrically varying hybrid models, as well as benchmark tests for computational costs of the proposed structures.",
